<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-1099 </DOCNO><TEXT>An analysis of 136 cases of stomach cancer led to the determination ofthe role and place of gammatopography, echography, computerized X-raytomography, angiography and laparoscopy in specified preoperative diagnosisof extraorganic spreading of primary tumors. The informative value andshortcomings of certain methods were shown. A high accuracy of the entireset of diagnostic procedures (94.8%) in the preoperative definition ofstomach cancer involvement of the abdominal and retroperitoneal organsand tissues was emphasized.</TEXT></DOC>